        <h2 class="text-center text-lg text-uppercase my-0">what is
          <strong>machine learning</strong>
        </h2>
        <hr class="divider">
        <img class="img-fluid float-left mr-4 d-none d-lg-block" src="../static/img/intro-pic.jpg" alt="">
        <p>Machine learning is a form programming in which the computer is given a basic parameters regarding the desired task and outcome, but where the computer learns through trial and error better and worse paths and solutions. One example of this many of use on a daily basis is through social media. If your picture is posted on Facebook, you could be tagged my name in the photo without ever writing a word. Facebook knows your face. They've seen your picture so many times that it has become recognizable. Nobody told the computer to tag you, the computer learned the unique curves of your face and decided to suggest that you are indeed the individual in the photo.</p>
        <p>With the slider puzzle, we have taught the machine the rules, shown the machine some ways that the game could be solved, and allowed the computer to play over and over again. Over time the machine is able to distinguish between a good move and bad move, resulting in a more efficient path to the solution.</p>
